Message:
Okay, I understand you're experiencing a headache.

To help me understand what might be causing it, can you describe the location of your headache? Is it all over your head, or is it concentrated in a specific area like your temples, forehead, or back of your head?

Okay, I understand. So the headache is all over your head.

Can you describe the type of pain you're experiencing? Is it a throbbing, sharp, dull, or squeezing sensation?

Okay, I understand. You're experiencing a throbbing headache all over your head.

On a scale of 1 to 10, with 1 being very mild and 10 being the worst headache you've ever experienced, how would you rate the pain?

Okay, I understand. You're experiencing a throbbing headache all over your head, and you rate the pain as a 10 out of 10. That sounds very intense.

Has anything else been bothering you? For example, have you experienced any nausea, vomiting, or sensitivity to light or sound?

Okay, I understand. You're experiencing a throbbing headache all over your head, you rate the pain as a 10 out of 10, and you are also experiencing sensitivity to light. Given the intensity and accompanying sensitivity to light, it could be a migraine.

How long have you had this headache? Is this a new experience, or have you had similar headaches in the past?

Okay, I understand. You're experiencing a throbbing headache all over your head, you rate the pain as a 10 out of 10, and you are also experiencing sensitivity to light. Given the intensity and accompanying sensitivity to light, it could be a migraine, and this is a new experience.

Are you experiencing any visual disturbances, such as blurred vision, seeing spots or flashing lights?

Okay, I understand. You're experiencing a throbbing headache all over your head, you rate the pain as a 10 out of 10, you are experiencing sensitivity to light and seeing floaters, and this is a new experience. Given the intensity, sensitivity to light, and visual disturbances, it could be a migraine.

Have you taken any medication for the headache, and if so, what was it and did it provide any relief?

Okay, I understand. You're experiencing a throbbing headache all over your head, you rate the pain as a 10 out of 10, you are experiencing sensitivity to light and seeing floaters, and this is a new experience. Given the intensity, sensitivity to light, and visual disturbances, it could be a migraine. You have also taken Tylenol.

Did the Tylenol provide any relief? If so, how much?
